### Q17: KG Query — Natural Language Parsing

**Cavab:** [query_natural_language()](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Desktop/SparkStack%20Systsems/Red%20Shadow%20Documents/red_shadow_v2.0/Red-Shadow/src/redclaw/memory/knowledge_graph.py#174-215) regex+keyword matching istifadə edir, LLM deyil.

#### Parsing Logic ([knowledge_graph.py#L174-L214](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Desktop/SparkStack%20Systsems/Red%20Shadow%20Documents/red_shadow_v2.0/Red-Shadow/src/redclaw/memory/knowledge_graph.py#L174-L214)):

```python
def query_natural_language(self, query: str) -> Dict:
    ip_match = re.search(r'\b(?:\d{1,3}\.){3}\d{1,3}\b', query)
    cve_match = re.search(r'CVE-\d{4}-\d{4,7}', query)

    if "vulnerabilities" in query_lower:
        return self.get_vulnerabilities_for_host(ip_match.group(0))
    elif "exploits" in query_lower:
        return self.get_exploits_for_cve(cve_match.group(0))
    elif "services" in query_lower:
        return self.get_services_for_host(ip_match.group(0))
    elif "attack" in query_lower and "path" in query_lower:
        return self.get_attack_path()
```

> **Nəticə:** Bu sadə keyword matching-dir. "Show me the weak spots" kimi fuzzy query-lər support olunmur.

